content:
When you enable Case Feed for your organization, an upgrade process converts active cases to the new interface and creates feed items for activity on those cases. This process is available in Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

During the upgrade process, users don't notice anything different. After it's complete, users with Case Feed see existing and new cases in the new interface, while others continue to see traditional cases.

The 5000 most recent, active cases are converted to the Case Feed interface. Older cases are also upgraded if they have comments, emails, or logged calls that were added within a specific date range. Up to 1500 additional cases can be converted, depending on their activity level.

The following items are added to the feed for each case: up to 60 email messages, up to 60 private and public comments, and up to 60 logged calls. The Case Feed interface is enabled for all new cases, giving users access to the publisher and feed.

You receive an email message when the upgrade process has finished. We recommend enabling Case Feed in a full-copy sandbox organization before your production org, and waiting until it's complete before giving users access.
title: Case Feed Upgrade Process in Service Cloud
